Reasoning: The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks and neural word embeddings, which are typically studied in the Computer Science sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of supervised disambiguation, which is a machine learning technique, and the training process of word-sense models, which are topics studied in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of Part-of-Speech disambiguated embeddings on neural dependency parsing, which is a task related to Natural Language Understanding (cs.NE) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
